title: Usage
text: input ggoncoplot data.frame 1 row per mutation. data.frame must contain columns describing following: Gene Symbol Sample Identifier (optional) mutation type (optional) tooltip (character string: show mouse hover particular mutation) columns can order, named anything. define mapping input dataset columns required features call ggoncoplot

title: Usage
code: # TCGA GBM dataset from TCGAmuations package gbm_csv <- system.file(package='ggoncoplot', "testdata/GBM_tcgamutations_mc3_maf.csv.gz") gbm_df <- read.csv(file = gbm_csv, header=TRUE)  gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode'   )

title: Usage
text: Colour mutation specifying col_mutation_type
code: # TCGA GBM dataset from TCGAmuations package gbm_csv <- system.file(package='ggoncoplot', "testdata/GBM_tcgamutations_mc3_maf.csv.gz") gbm_df <- read.csv(file = gbm_csv, header=TRUE)  gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification'   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: Show 4 frequently mutated genes using topn argument
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      topn = 4   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: Use genes_to_ignore argument filter specific genes, TTN MUC16. can use packages like somaticflags get lists genes might want filter .
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      topn = 10,     genes_to_ignore = c("TTN", "MUC16")   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 9 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/9 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 9/9 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: lets show TP53 TERT
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      genes_to_include = c('TP53', 'TERT'),   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 6 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/6 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 6/6 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: show_all_samples argument add samples don’t mutations selected genes plot. Note supply metadata table, default samples lacking mutations still shown. can include samples setting metadata_require_mutations = FALSE isn’t recommended unless ’re sure sample truly mutations dataframe.
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      show_all_samples = TRUE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text:
Use col_tooltip argument indicate column input dataframe used custom tooltip. Note tooltips html, want insert break, just paste
. Similarly, want make text tooltip bold, try "text_to_bold<\b>". Note single sample multiple mutations gene, represented one tile oncoplot, tooltip mutation shown (newline delimited).
code: gbm_df |>    mutate(tooltip = paste0(Chromosome, ":", Start_Position, " ", Reference_Allele, ">", Tumor_Seq_Allele2)) |>   ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      col_tooltip = 'tooltip' # We'll specify a custom tooltip based on our new 'tooltip' column   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: many samples mutations Gene (optionally coloured mutation type)
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',     draw_gene_barplot = TRUE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: can use set draw_tmb_barplot = TRUE plot total number mutations (total mutational burden) sample. datasets, presence one hypermutator makes hard see less extreme trends, defualt mutational burden plotted log10 scale. can changed setting log10_transform_tmb = FALSE
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',     draw_tmb_barplot = TRUE,      #log10_transform_tmb = FALSE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete #> ! TMB plot: Ignoring `col_mutation_type` since `log10_transform = TRUE`. #> This is because you cannot accurately plot stacked bars on a logarithmic scale

what: Add both TMB and and Gene Barplots
title: Usage
text: Usually, ’ll want draw margin plots (tmb + gene).
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',     draw_tmb_barplot = TRUE,      #log10_transform_tmb = FALSE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete #> ! TMB plot: Ignoring `col_mutation_type` since `log10_transform = TRUE`. #> This is because you cannot accurately plot stacked bars on a logarithmic scale

title: Usage
code: gbm_clinical_csv <- system.file(  package = "ggoncoplot",  "testdata/GBM_tcgamutations_mc3_clinical.csv" )  gbm_clinical_df <- read.csv(file = gbm_clinical_csv, header = TRUE)  ggoncoplot(  gbm_df,  col_genes = "Hugo_Symbol",  col_samples = "Tumor_Sample_Barcode",  col_mutation_type = "Variant_Classification",  metadata = gbm_clinical_df,  cols_to_plot_metadata = c('gender', 'histological_type', 'prior_glioma', 'tumor_tissue_site'),   draw_tmb_barplot = TRUE,   draw_gene_barplot = TRUE,   show_all_samples = TRUE ) #> ℹ 2 samples with metadata have no mutations. Fitering these out #> ℹ To keep these samples, set `metadata_require_mutations = FALSE`. To view them in the oncoplot ensure you additionally set `show_all_samples = TRUE` #> → TCGA-06-0165-01A-01D-1491-08 #> → TCGA-06-0167-01A-01D-1491-08 #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete #> ! TMB plot: Ignoring `col_mutation_type` since `log10_transform = TRUE`. #> This is because you cannot accurately plot stacked bars on a logarithmic scale

title: GG oncoplot — ggoncoplot
text: .data data oncoplot. data.frame 1 row per mutation cohort. Must contain columns describing gene_symbols sample_identifiers (data.frame) col_genes name data column containing gene names/symbols (string) col_samples name data column containing sample identifiers (string) col_mutation_type name data column describing mutation types (string) genes_to_include specific genes include oncoplot (character) genes_to_ignore names genes ignored (character) col_tooltip name data column containing whatever information want display (string) topn many top genes visualise. Ignored genes_to_include supplied (number) return_extra_genes_if_tied instead strictly returning topn genes, case ties (multiple genes mutated exact number samples, complicating selection top n genes), return tied genes (potentially topn). FALSE, return strictly topn genes, breaking ties based order appearance dataset (flag) palette named vector mapping possible mutation types (vector names) colours (vector values). metadata_palette list named vectors. List names correspond metadata column names (categorical ). Vector names levels columns. Vector values colours, vector names used map values .data colour. supplied ggoncoplot check values either valid MAF variant classification terms use pre-made colour schemes ontologies mutationtypes package. mutation type terms described using ontologies, 12 colour RColourBrewer palette used, user warned make custom mapping force consistent colour schemes plots (character) metadata_colours_default default colours use different levels metadata. used colour variables palette supplied. metadata_colours_default_logical colours binary variables metadata (vector 2 colors elements represent colours TRUE FALSE respectively) (character) metadata_colours_missing colour use values NA (string) metadata dataframe describing sample level metadata. One column must contain unique sample identifiers. columns can describe numeric / categorical metadata (data.frame) col_samples_metadata column metadata data.frame describes sample identifiers (string) cols_to_plot_metadata names columns metadata plotted (character) metadata_require_mutations filter samples metadata lacking mutations .data (flag) show_sample_ids show sample_ids_on_x_axis (flag) interactive plot interactive (boolean) interactive_svg_width dimensions interactive plot (number) interactive_svg_height dimensions interactive plot (number) xlab_title x axis lable. Set xlab_title = NULL remove title (string) ylab_title y axis interactive plot. Set ylab_title = NULL remove title (string) fontsize_xlab size x axis title (number) fontsize_ylab size y axis title (number) fontsize_genes size y axis text (gene names) (number) fontsize_samples size x axis text (sample names). Ignored unless show_sample_ids set true (number) fontsize_count fontsize gene mutation count x axis (number) fontsize_tmb_title fontsize y axis title TMB marginal plot (number) fontsize_tmb_axis fontsize y axis text TMB marginal plot (number) tile_height proportion available vertical space tile take (0-1) (number) tile_width proportion available horizontal space  tile take (0-1) (number) colour_backround colour used background non-mutated tiles (string) colour_mutation_type_unspecified colour mutations oncoplot margin plots col_mutation_type supplied (string) draw_gene_barplot add barplot describing number samples gene mutated (right side) (flag) draw_tmb_barplot add barplot describing total number mutations sample (main plot). single gene mutated multiple times, mutations counted towards total (flag) show_ylab_title show y axis title oncoplot (flag) show_xlab_title show x axis title oncoplot (flag) show_ylab_title_tmb show y axis title TMB margin plot (flag) show_axis_gene show x axis line/ticks/labels gene barplot (flag) show_axis_tmb show y axis line/ticks/labels TMB barplot (flag) log10_transform_tmb log10 transform total number mutations TMB marginal plot (flag) even mutations selected genes. Samples described metadata mutations still filtered default, can show setting metadata_require_mutations = FALSE  (flag) scientific_tmb display tmb counts scientific notation (flag) show_all_samples show samples oncoplot, plotsize_tmb_rel_height percentage vertical space TMB margin plot take . Must value 5-90 (number) plotsize_gene_rel_width percentage horizontal space gene barplot take . title: Prep data for oncoplot — ggoncoplot_prep_df

title: Prep data for oncoplot — ggoncoplot_prep_df
code: ggoncoplot_prep_df(   .data,   col_genes,   col_samples,   genes_for_oncoplot,   col_mutation_type = NULL,   col_tooltip = col_samples,   verbose = TRUE )

title: Prep data for oncoplot — ggoncoplot_prep_df
text: .data data oncoplot. data.frame 1 row per mutation cohort. Must contain columns describing gene_symbols sample_identifiers (data.frame) col_genes name data column containing gene names/symbols (string) col_samples name data column containing sample identifiers (string) genes_for_oncoplot list genes include oncoplot (character). col_mutation_type name data column describing mutation types (string) col_tooltip name data column containing whatever information want display (string) verbose verbose mode (flag)

title: Prep data for oncoplot — ggoncoplot_prep_df

title: Generate score based on genes — score_based_on_gene_rank
code: if (FALSE) { # First set of genes has a high rank since both BRCA2 and EGFR are mutated score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "EGFR", "PTEN", "BRCA2"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2)  # If EGFR is mutated without BRCA2, we get a lower score score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "EGFR", "PTEN", "IDH1"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2)  # If BRCA2 is mutated without EGFR, # we get a score lower than BRCA2+EGFR but higher than EGFR alone due to higher gene_rank of BRCA2 score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "IDH1", "PTEN", "BRCA2"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2) }
